postcontent: What I have for sale is a Glock 19 Gen 4 with a few little upgrades and one big one, which is the "with or without" part of the title.  To cover that part right off, we're talking about the latest generation Lasermax Guide Rod Green Pulsed Laser.  As you know, this item replaces the stock guide rod and the beam exits where the guide rod plug would be, directly under the barrel.  It is invisible from the outside of the gun so you can use your favorite G19 holster.  Look up Lasermax and see what you think and note the pricing.  They are not cheap but you get what you pay for. Makes it a LOT easier than the flat little unit they ship with.  I recently installed the Tango Down Vickers rear slide plate that simply extends about 1/8th of an inch on each side at the rear of the slide so that it can be racked with wet or otherwise slippery hands or even against a belt or boot heel.  I can easily remove that if your prefer.  Comes with factory box, 2 factory Gen 4 mags, backstraps, cleaning rod/brush, paperwork; everything that came with it.  I'd like $525 for it without the laser.  Add $225 if you want the laser.  Laser is very new and I have fired exactly one (1) round using it. title: For Sale:  FDE Glock 19 (gen 3)
postcontent: This is a Glock 19 gen 3 with 2 15 round magazines. It has a Trijicon front night sight and Tru-Glo back sights. These are fresh night sights and very bright. The reason that i mixed them was that the front Trijicon is slightly smaller than the Tru-glo back sights and that makes it very easy to pick up the sight picture in low light situations. It also has an oversized slide stop on it. This G-19 is in great shape and has had less than 2 boxes of ammo through it. It is sighted in and really accurate at around 20 yards. The only reason that i'm selling it is that I have 2 of them in FDE and just can't justify keeping both. I have had gen 3 and gen 4 Glocks and actually really prefer the gen 3's.. they just seem to have a better trigger and feel to them (in my opinion). Anyhow, this one is a great shooter and has the somewhat rare flat dark earth frame. Thanks for looking and MERRY Christmas!
